{
  "##reservoir_header##" : "¡Bien hecho! Tus granjas están en marcha, y tus ciudadanos tiene comida. Ahora es el momento de expandir tu asentamiento.\nAgua\n Construye un deposito junto al agua. Se llenará de agua si tu asesor laboral ha asignado suficientes trabajadores para los servicios de agua."
  "##reservoir_build_second##" : "Para construir un segundo deposito, selecciona otra vez deposito del botón de estructuras de agua. Entonces mueve el puntero del ratón sobre el primer deposito que has construido hasta que veas un cuadrado verde alrededor. Manten pulsado el botón y 'arrastra' el cursor hasta la posición deseada. Verás un segundo deposito, conectado mediante un acueducto al primero."
  "##reservoir_citizens_like_fountain##" : "Tus ciudadanos prefieren tener una fuente para su agua más que un pozo. Las fuentes dan agua más limpia, y abastecen un area mayor que los pozos. Hay muchos informes de superposición para ayudarte a gestionar tu ciudad. El juego continua funcionando mientras se muestran las superposiciones. Cuando se usa una superposición, pulsa la barra espaciadora para ver toda la ciudad temporalmente. Manten tu puntero sobre un objeto del mapa, y un texto explicara lo que significa para esa superposición."
  "##can_build_gardens##" : "Ahora puedes construir más edificios. Las casas de baños necesitan estar al alcance de un deposito y tener acceso a empleados."
  "##gardens_get_desirable##" : "Los jardines hacen un area más deseable."
  "##can_build_theaters##" : "Los teatros son un lugar de entretenimiento popular, pero necesitan actores para las actuaciones. Construye una colonia de actores para suministrarlos."
  "##build_more_farms##" : "No olvides construir nuevas granjas antes de que te quedes sin comida."
  "##tax_tutorial##" : "Money. Building and running elites costs mioney. Rome gives you enough denarii to get started - but it won't be enough to complete your assignment.Taxes are an important source of income. Eventually, your city will grow beyond the Senate's tax collector routes. Build forums as bases for additional tax inspectors in other parts of your town."
  "##nice_house_pay_more##" : "Mejores casas pagan mas impuestos."
  "##tt_advisors##" : "Asesores."
  "##tt2_caption##" : "Metas inmediatas: Construye un granero y llenalo de trigo"
  "##tutorial_markets_text##" : "Your priorities should be security, housing, food, and water, in that order. Without housing and food, new immigrants will not move in to your city.\nRome now wishes your city to grow food. Build a farm on fertile land - look for the yellow tufts that indicate this. Connect it to housing with path. If the housing is too far away, farm will not ge access to labor."
  "##tutorial_granary_text##" : "Build a granary new to the farm, and make sure that it, too, has access to labor."
  "##tutorial_granary_text2##" : "When the wheat is ripe, a cart will carry it to the granary. Gradually the granary will fill up. The fewer empty windows you can see, the fuller the granary is."
  "##tutorial_priority##" : "Markets.\nBuild a market fairly near granary. Once it has enough employees, it generate market traders, who walk the roads near market. One if these traders brings foor from granary back to the marketm provide the granary if not too far away. The other trader walks past houses, distributing the food. Later on, when your city has warehouses with manufactured goods, these save market will distribute commodities the same way they handle food"
  "##adviser_panel##" : "Click the advisors button to consult the helpful aides whe help you manage your city. The Chief advisor summarizes your whole city, highlightin area which need your attention. Your labor advisor lets you change the allocation of labor, or the wage rate you city pays. Visit them all, just to see what is there."
  "##tt_industry##" : "Industry\n Now build a clay pit close to water, and a warehouse nearby. Connect them to housing as usual, and before long a cart will take clay to the warehouse."
  "##tt_build_pottery##" : "You can also build a pottery workshop, to turn clay into pottery. When the pottery is ready, a cart takes it to nearest warehouse. From there, market traders will take it if there is demand for it in your town, and distribute it just as they do food. Higher-level housing demands pottery. Build two pottery workshops to use all of the clay pit can produce."
  "##trade_enabled_tt##" : "Well done! You now have successfull industry in your town. Now you can turn that into cash. \n\n Trade. \n Trade can be both a major source of income for a city, and a source of desired goods. Click the empire map button to see a map of Roman Empire and its surroundings."
  "##open_traderoute_tutorial##" : "Right now, Rome hardly has any Empire at all, so you will only see a few cities on the map; your success will jelp ot to grow later/ The city with a black and gold glag is yours; the city with a red flag is one happy to trade with you. Click on it to see which products it is prepared to buy from you or sel to you. Click to open a  trade route (which will cost some money)"
  "##tt_goto_trade_advisor##" : "Now, go to your Trade Advisor."
  "##tt_set_export_rules##" : "Click on the small picture of pottery to see how many you have stored at your warehouse. Click on the 'not trading' button, and it will change to 'Export over' and some arrows; click on the arrows until it says 'Export Over 2'"
  "##tt2_first_export_sale##" : "This authorize the sale of any pottery in your warehouse in excess of 2 cart loads. Exit to the main game now, and before long you will see a donkey train move througth your city. If you have more then 2 carts of pottery in your warehouse, it will stop and remove it, paying you at the same time. Your first export sale!"
  "##tt2_expand_your_city##" : "You can now expand your city futher, with income from taxes and pottery sales financing your growth."
